senses.sense_definition: Having a specific kind or number of naves, typically referring to the central part of a church building.

examples.text: The historic basilica is a triple-<w>naved</w> building with high ceilings and intricate stonework.
Architects designed a simple, single-<w>naved</w> chapel for the small rural community.

senses.sense_definition: A male given name of Persian and Urdu origin.

examples.text: <w>Naved</w> introduced himself to the new team members at the morning meeting.
We are waiting for <w>Naved</w> to arrive before we start the celebration.
